Seeing this Students for Warnock Press Conference go from vision to reality was PHENOMENAL. I was able to select students from 8+ universities to come together to represent in front of multiple news stations urging their peers and youth statewide to GET OUT AND VOTE! I’m so thankful for the amazing support and effort of our campaign team for making sure this was executed successfully✊🏾 I never get to post the million things I get to do being the Director of Youth Engagement for  this historical campaign but If you want a sneak peek tap through my highlights 💜 NOW, GEORGIA LETS VOTE!!!!! THE YOUTH VOTE MATTERS & WE ARE NOT BACKING DOWN! ✊🏾✊🏾✊🏾

#TeamWarnock 🗣

GEORGIA WE WON!!! Working for this campaign as the Statewide Director of Youth Engagement has been the honor of a lifetime being apart of such HISTORY! 
IT WAS NOT EASY BUT TEAM WARNOCK DID THAT!!!!! Being able to ORGANIZE, MOBILIZE, & EMPOWER THOUSANDS of young people across the STATE while being able to give them sooooo many once in a lifetime opportunities is what I’m SOOO GRATEFUL for! WE JUST SECURED THE FIRST BLACK SENATOR OF GEORGIA IN OFFICE FOR 👏🏾SIX 👏🏾YEARS 👏🏾👏🏾👏🏾 We sacrificed SOOOO much for this work and LAST NIGHT GOD SAID I WILL SHOW YALL WHY!!!!!!!!! WE SENT WALKER BACK WALKING TO TEXAS BABY!!!!!! 

For SEVEN years I have been INVESTED in this work since I was 18 and I’m so glad we secured this seat FOR OUR SENATOR @raphaelwarnock 🔥👏🏾

& to my POLITICAL DIRECTOR @officialzenobia , YOU CHANGED MY LIFE AND I PLEAD THE BLOOD OF JESUS OVER YOU AND YOU LEADERSHIP YOU ARE A CONQUEROR!!!! WHAT YOU DO TO UPHOLD DEMOCRACY IS UNMATCHED, THE WAY YOU BELIEVE IN YOUR TEAM IS UNMATCHED! YOU LEAD US TO VICTORY ZENOBIA WE DID IT!!!!!!🔥🔥🔥🔥🔥🔥

TO EVERY STUDENT THAT I WORKED ON THIS CAMPAIGN WITH, I LOVE YOU I THANK YOU AND YOU WILL ALWAYS HAVE ME BY YOUR SIDE I GOT YALL FOREVER. 

I graduated from Clark atlanta university, it’s no wonder we found a way or made one 😝

I am SO thankful to have been invited to The White House Holiday Party by @futurecoalition, a phenomenal Youth Empowerment Organization! They flew out myself along with four other Georgia Youth Organizers to DC for such an iconic moment⭐️ 

I am so thankful to have sisters in this movement like @ms.primaryy  who made sure I was amongst the group selected and the feeling of gratefulness that Brings me is just inexplicable🥺💜

25 years ago I was born in Jamaica Queens Hospital to two haitian immigrants who came to this country as teenagers SPEAKING NO ENGLISH, I NEVER thought these things would be my reality but I’m so grateful to the blood of Jesus for continuing to elevate me beyond my wildest dreams. 

1 year ago I was so low to that point I thought my life was over but I KEPT manifesting God would do a NEW thing in 2022 and by his GRACE&FAVOR, THAT IS ALL HE HAS DONE! 2023 is NOT READY FOR ME ⭐️

Watching this Tory Lanez Trial has been nothing short of TRIGGERING, TRAUMATIZING, and disturbing to say the least. To every black girl and woman out there who has ever questioned confronting or reporting their abuser or assaulter, please know there is a community that SEES YOU AND SUPPORTS YOU no matter what our society has shown you they will try and do if you speak up.  To every single WOMAN please know you are BOT DEFINED BY YOUR PAST and only YOU and GOD can determine your future. 

I pray to the lord that Megan has some sense of peace even though I can only imagine the mental turmoil this case has caused her. 🥺🙏🏾

My 1st NEPHEW-SUN ☀️ Josiah is the BEST view I’ve seen all year no matter the seas I have traveled from Africa to the White House, witnessing my first born nephew and knowing I will forever be his AUNTY is my life’s pride and joy. JOSIAH was born to this world TWO MONTHS early and as you can see he is now a chunka wunka 9 month old miracle baby. 

I sacrifice a lot to be away from my family here in ATL and  This year I was blessed to reach the best career accomplishments but the number one thing I’m proud of is how I make my nephew laugh and how I have a special song I made for him that soothes his soul so much❤️ My sister is doing an amazing job raising our baby, and she’s an OBGYN saving woman and babies and daily. I see you sis, you’re killing it boo 😘🦋

My Legacy, and alongside my little brother they are my true first-borns😭 IM OBSESSED! IM AUNTY KEENA 😭

#AuntyLove ⭐️💜

I was 17 years old when I moved to Atlanta by myself 8 years ago, You cannot tell me the blood of Jesus is not REAL. I knew ONE person and I had never even stepped FOOT in this city. I graduated High school with a 1.7 gpa, but I just KNEW God had a new purpose coming for my life. My childhood was so rough & dark, my #1 promise to myself was ALWAYS that after high school I would give myself the life I deserve & I just cannot believe that God has given me the opportunity to do that and so much more everyday. Through every drop of blood, sweat, and tears that I pour into my work and my community, im now learning how to pour that same love and effort into myself, it feels new but I’m digging it 💖 I’m reminded by God each day that my purpose is so much greater than myself.  I like to write long captions because I never want people to look at me and think my wins have come easily or smoothly, I just have a refusal to give up a refusal to have doors slammed in my face and I will not stop until I WIN. I will continue the work of my immigrant parents and build a mighty legacy for future family. 

Thank you all SOOOO much for all of the birthday love I received from you all it means more than to me when you will ever know. 💖

Now, see you all NEXT THURSDAY at ATL’s BEST networking experience- @TheCultureMyxr 💃🏾💃🏾💃🏾💃🏾💃🏾💃🏾💃🏾

“There’s a time to sing, and a time to SWING” - Malcolm X ✊🏾 This historical context in this video  is so important to note that it was no coincidence that the spirit of our ancestors were rejoicing seeing our community bond and attack against such a cruel act of violence against our own. Our community never gets to see Justice, the black king lived AND got to see his whole community go to BAT for him on the same dock our ancestors were beat and sold!!!!! 

Everyday as black people we are subjected to seeing our people being killed, beaten, and mistreated for the color of our skin and we it often makes us feel hopeless. A lot of us can’t wait to witness some racist ish because we not recording we jumping straight in that 💯 In the video we saw a black men get brutally beaten by a group of white men for doing his job, and we actually got to see STREET JUSTICE be served in the very same clip. They could’ve killed that man And we would have been collectively mourning as we always do, but no my people finally get to be collectively happy about something, seeing our people stick together!!!!!!!! 

This is what community is all about, we need to always protect our own. I always knew I loved me some Alabama 😅💖 

I’m going live to talk about this again we need to further dissect because I think it’s so important people understand why we are really rejoicing as a community, this is one of the only happy ending we’ve ever got to see and we’re forced to see things like this everyday. So many innocent black people would’ve been alive today if they had this same group of amazing warriors who came to defense in Alabama.🙏🏾
